                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“For I am the LORD, I do not change; Therefore you are not consumed, O sons of Jacob.”
                                                                            <b>Malachi 3:6 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and comes down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow of turning.”
                                                                            <b>James 1:17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever.”
                                                                            <b>Hebrews 13:8 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Immutable means constant and unchanging, not subject to change or variation in form or quality or nature.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God is the only one that can claim “I change not.”  In order for God to change He would have to go from better to best, or from great to greater, from Holy to Holier.  This is impossible because God is already the best, He is already great, if he needed to become better or greater He would be in competition with someone who is great.  There is no one greater or better than God .  And He can’t become “more Holy”. He is Holiness.  God remains infinitely Holy and forever unchanging.  If He could change in any way, then He could not be the <b>LORD GOD ALMIGHTY</b>.   Aren’t you glad? I am.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We on the other hand are mutable, we are subject to change or variation in form or quality or nature.  From conception to death we change physical, emotionally, mentally and spiritually.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Reprimanding one of my children one day in full blown corrective criticism mode I looked and said, “when did you get so tall?”  I was taken back because I hadn’t noticed the growth spurt that now had me looking up at her.   Change over time can be subtle and take us by surprise.  Other changes we can pick up moment by moment.  Change is a necessary part of life, but not for God who is life.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Yes Jesus did step over from eternity and was clothed in humanity.  This did not change God’s immutability.  Jesus was clothed in flesh yet His deity didn’t become humanity.  He was one hundred percent God, and one hundred percent man.  What is not God can not become God, that which is God can not become that which is not God .  When we accept Christ as our savior and Lord, we do not become God.  He dwells within us.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Usually we are never satisfied with ourselves...there is one change that we can seek out that will change everything else in our lives.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“But we all, with unveiled face, beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into the same image from glory to glory, just as by the Spirit of the Lord.”
                                                                            <b>II Corinthians 3:18 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Are we willing to have an unveiled face, meaning an open relationship with God.  Looking at who we are and allowing Him to transform (change) us from the inside out as we spend time beholding the glory of the God of grace, love, peace, righteousness we will then begin to see grace, love, peace and righteousness taking root in us.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father today we come before you seeking change.  As we look into the mirror of your word we want to desire the changes to become more apparent in our lives that others would witness the glory that has transformed us and will continue to transform us into Your image.  Be glorified in our lives Lord.  Amen
                                                                        </p>
